
[1]quibble

   QUIB'BLE, n.

   1. A start or turn from the point in question, or from plain truth; an
   evasion; a cavil; a pretense; as, to answer a sound argument by
   quibbles.

   Quirks and quibbles have no place in the search after truth.

   2. A pun; a low conceit.

                               QUIB'BLE, v.i.

   1. To evade the point in question, or plain truth, by artifice, play
   upon words, caviling or any conceit; to trifle in argument or
   discourse.

   2. To pun.
